      "id": "PopularPost375351",
      "post_content": "Macar is one of the best cards in Journey for draft.  \n  \nRemoval in limited is always valuable. [Gild](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Gild) itself is quite valuable, since it can get rid of a creature pretty efficiently. A creature that has the capability to remove a creature *each turn* **for free** (essentially) is extremely valuable.  \n  \nMacar just needs either one free attack step or a conduit of tapping. [Weirdly](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378419), [I](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=380495) [think](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378534) [Theros](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378497) [has](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378473) [quite](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378436) [a](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=74306) [few](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=373622) [ways](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378533) [to](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=73947) [tap](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=378410) [your](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=1) own/auto... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Ferlord",
